cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.GT, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new deep reinforcement learning framework. It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with learning in a hybrid action space. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics) as it applies the proposed framework to a simulated RoboCup soccer scenario. It may also be relevant to cs.GT (Game Theory) as it applies the framework to a computer game scenario. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it applies the framework to a game with visual inputs (King of Glory).
